description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Band 6 Social Worker to join the Perinatal Community Mental Health Team. The post is to cover a one-year maternity leave, a fixed term at 30 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Social Worker with a strong knowledge of family systems, of parent-infant relationships, attachment theory and Safeguarding practices. The Perinatal Community Mental Health clinicians will be relying on your expertise in Safeguarding processes, to assist with writing Child Protection reports, to co-work cases which are active to Children Services, to attend Safeguarding MDT meetings in health and social care settings and to chair Safeguarding group supervision activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be expected to hold a caseload, to provide initial and comprehensive assessments, to complete risk assessments and care plans as well as to provide various clinical interventions to women during their Perinatal Pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Perinatal Community Mental Health services provide prevention, detection and management of mental health problems that complicate pregnancy and the postpartum year. These include new-onset problems, recurrences of previous problems in women who have been well for some time and in women with existing mental health problems who become pregnant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Promoting the relationship with the infant and its emotional, physical well-being and development are central to the care provided by perinatal mental health services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Perinatal Community Mental Health service offers an exciting opportunity to work within a specialist multi-disciplinary setting, working closely with key partners in health, social care and other sectors. The service offers a wide range of MDT clinical assessments and treatments, specific specialist perinatal therapeutic individual and group interventions. We promote a strong service user led participation culture as well as supporting partners and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity and offers you a chance to progress with your career. The service provides education and training opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kirsty Hogarth, CFYP Leadership Support Co-ordinator: kirsty.hogarth@nsft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
